examples.sentence: I miei collaboratori mi hanno aiutato molto con questo progetto.
examples.translation: My collaborators helped me a lot with this project.

etymology.value: Italian: from collaborare (to collaborate) + -tori (suffix forming nouns referring to people).

usage_notes.explanation: This is the plural form of the Italian word 'collaboratore', meaning 'collaborator'. It refers to multiple people working together on a project or endeavor.

readability_explanation.text: This is an Italian word, so readability depends on familiarity with the Italian language.
